                     <interp inst="t18250113-77-person445" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an apprentice to Mr. Martillo, a tailor. I saw the prisoner at my master's shop on Thursday and on Friday - on Thursday, the 23d of December,<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182501130030"></xptr>he brought a time-piece to our house, No. 10, New-street, Covent-garden; I did not notice it particularly - it was mahogany, and round at the top; he offered it for sale to the men at the shop; he had formerly worked there; he left it from Thursday till Friday.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 19.</p>
